      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROYAL GUARDIAN (7) missed by 1.3L two back before a 0.7L defeat when dropping back to 1300m last time out. Back up to 1400m today, but gets the blinkers on for the first time after jumping favourite last time out. Can lob in a handy position for Faithfull and go one better this time. MAD SPITFIRE (1) comes through the same races as ROYAL GUARDIAN where he has finished behind her on both occasions. Needs a touch of luck from the draw, but the claim of Cheung comes in handy and he won't be far away. QUIET GODDESS (6) is third-up here and should appreciate this easier assignment. She's now with the David Smith barn and she still has some upside being a lightly raced mare. Wouldn't surprise to see her in the finish. LANTA (2) is better than he showed last time out when tiring late in the race. May not have handled the quick turnaround there. Expect sharp improvement. I'M COOL TWO (4) can improve with the blinkers on first time.",
